AB  - As the importance of ESG factors in port operations becomes increasingly apparent and environmental issues become more prominent, this paper proposes a decision-making model to assess the green progress of ports. The model employs a probabilistic linguistic binary set and an improved PROMETHEE II method to evaluate factors such as environmental quality and governance. By integrating data from official institutions like the Ministry of Transport of China and ESG reports from authorities, the paper evaluates the green development status of seven Chinese ports as case studies to validate the model's performance. The results demonstrate the effectiveness and scientific validity of the proposed method. According to the evaluation, Tianjin Port is leading, while Dalian Port requires improvement. The study recommends that port managers adopt green strategies, collaborate with supply chains, and share resources to facilitate industry transformation. It also underscores the necessity of policy incentives for port greening and transformation. © 2025 Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.
