AB  - This paper proposes a systematic, integrated process mining (PM)/data envelopment analysis (DEA) approach to the evaluation of the discrepancy between planned and actual container workflows (CWs) at a container terminal. The proposed approach extracts, from the databases of a terminal information system, log data in which it detects actual CWs. Subsequently, it evaluates the discrepancy between the planned and actual CWs. This paper shows how to utilize event data in generating actual performed CWs and to evaluate the discrepancy between planned and actual CWs in terms of multi-factor performance. We illustrate the proposed approach by applying it to a Korean container terminal's actual event data. © ILS 2018 - Information Systems, Logistics and Supply Chain, Proceedings. All rights reserved.
