AB  - Different devices and systems often use different data formats and protocols, so the compatibility of different data formats is the main difficulty in bidirectional conversion. Therefore, a bidirectional conversion method of smart port equipment operation data based on element tree is proposed. The element tree is used to complete the bidirectional transformation of the probabilistic relational data model and probabilistic XML data model of the operation data of the smart port equipment. The mapping relationship between the element tree and element nodes and various types of data models is established first, and the bidirectional transformation of the data model is realized on the premise of the element tree and mapping relationship. The experimental results show that the data exchange can be realized for the equipment information database and the operation state database of the port company. The query performance and write performance of bidirectional data exchange with different port transmission frequencies are better. In the process of bidirectional data conversion, the probability of data leakage is very low.  © 2023 ACM.
