AB  - This paper uses Data Envelopment Analysis (DEA) to empirically analysis the efficiency of Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei traffic integration and the results are as follows. Firstly, the railway network is running well while the difficulties to alleviate the contradiction between supply and demand of the highway transport has existed for a long time, and the homogenization of competition in the port construction is one of the burning issues of our times. Secondly, the scale ratio of transportation system within the region is not reasonably adapted, and increasing infrastructure investment is conducive to the rapid advance of the regional integration at present. Finally, according to the issues above, this paper proposes three suggestions. © 2017 IEEE.
